# Break and Continue in Java
In Java, the `break` and `continue` statements are used to control the flow of

for (int i = 1; i <= 10; i++) {
    if (i == 5) break;     // stops loop
    System.out.println(i);
}

# continue example

for (int i = 1; i <= 5; i++) {
    if (i == 3) continue;  // skips 3
    System.out.println(i);
}